===Ornithopods=== {| class="wikitable" align="center" width="100%" |- ! colspan="5" align="center" |[[Ornithopoda]] of the Turonian |- ! Taxa ! Presence ! Location ! Description ! Images |- | ''[[Anabisetia]]'' | | [[Cerro Lisandro Formation]], [[Neuquén Province]], Patagonia, Argentina | A {{convert|2|m|ft}} long [[elasmaria]]n | rowspan="100" |[[File:Anabisetia.jpg|thumb|center|200px|''[[Anabisetia]]'']][[Image:Bactrosaurus.JPG|thumb|center|200px|''[[Bactrosaurus]]'']][[File:Jeyawati NT.jpg|thumb|''[[Jeyawati]]'']] |- | ''[[Bactrosaurus]]'' | Turonian to [[Coniacian]] | [[Gobi Desert]], Mongolia and China | Would have been {{convert|6|m|ft|abbr=on}} long[1] and {{convert|2|m|ft|abbr=on}} high when in the quadrupedal stance, and weighed {{convert|1100|–|1500|kg|lb|abbr=on}}. Like many hadrosaurs, it could switch between bipedal and quadrupedal stances, but unusually it had large spines protruding from the vertebrae. |- |''[[Jeyawati]]'' |Turonian |[[Moreno Hill Formation]], New Mexico |A basal hadrosauroid |- | ''[[Macrogryphosaurus]]'' | Turonian to early [[Coniacian]] | [[Portezuelo Formation]], Argentina | A genus of basal iguanodont, a large bipedal herbivore |- | ''[[Notohypsilophodon]]'' | [[Cenomanian]]-Turonian | [[Bajo Barreal Formation]], Chubut, Argentina | A hypsilophodontid or other basal ornithopod, Notohypsilophodon would have been a bipedal herbivore. Its size has not been estimated |- | ''[[Shuangmiaosaurus]]'' | [[Cenomanian]]-Turonian | China | A poorly known [[iguanodont]] |}
===Plesiosaurs=== {| class="wikitable" align="center" width="100%" |- ! colspan="5" align="center" |[[Plesiosauria]] of the Turonian |- ! Taxa ! Presence ! Location ! Description ! Images |- | ''[[Brachauchenius]]'' | | [[Ottawa County, Kansas]] |''Brachauchenius'' represents the last known occurrence of a pliosaur in North America. | rowspan="99" |[[Image:Libonectes BW.jpg|thumb|center|200px|''[[Libonectes]]'']] [[Image:Polyptychodon hudsDB2.jpg|thumb|center|200px|''[[Polyptychodon]]'']] [[Image:Thililua BW.jpg|thumb|center|200px|''[[Thililua]]'']] |- | ''[[Libonectes]]'' | | [[Britton Formation]] ([[Cedar Hill, Texas|Cedar Hill]]), Texas, USA | A {{convert|7|–|14|m|ft|abbr=on}} long creature, was very similar to the related [[Elasmosaurus]]. It had a compact body with a short tail and large flippers. Its small skull had long, forward-facing teeth ideal for catching slippery fish and squid that came together outside of its mouth when the mouth was closed, and was placed atop a very long neck. |- | ''[[Manemergus]]'' | | Morocco | A genus of polycotylid plesiosaur |- | ''[[Megacephalosaurus]]'' | | [[Carlile Shale]], [[Russell County, Kansas]] | |- | ''[[Polyptychodon]] hudsoni'' | | Texas, USA | A {{convert|10|m|ft}} long Brachaucheniin pliosaurid |- | ''[[Thililua]]'' | | [[High Atlas]], Morocco | A genus of polycotylid plesiosaur, the estimated total length of Thililua is 5.5 to 6 metres. |}
